05160nam a22008655i 9781501505881DE-B159720230228123812.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230228t20172017gw     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)989860244  a97815015058817 a10.1515/97815015058812doi  a(DE-B1597)479493  a(OCoLC)988767611  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLAN0090002bisacsh1 aTrotzke, Andreas , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Grammar of Emphasis :bFrom Information Structure to the Expressive Dimension /cAndreas Trotzke. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2017] 4c©2017  a1 online resource (VIII, 192 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStudies in Generative Grammar [SGG] ,x0167-4331 ;v13100tFrontmatter -- tPreface -- tContents -- tI. The notion of emphasis -- t1. Introduction -- t2. The notion of emphasis for intensity -- tII. Empirical domains of emphasis -- t3. Particle topicalization and emphasis for intensity -- t4. Emphasis for intensity across clause types -- tIII. A unified account of emphasis -- t5. Emphasis and German clause structure -- t6. Conclusion: From information structure to the expressive dimension -- tReferences -- tAppendix A -- tAppendix B -- tAppendix C -- tAppendix D -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book reconsiders the linguistic notion of emphasis. For many, the concept of emphasis is confined to information structure. However, our understanding of the grammatical reflexes of emphasis is only partial as long as the expressive side of utterances is not taken into account. The book explores similarities, differences, and interactions between information structure and the expressive dimension of language in the domain of natural language grammar. Specifically, this monograph demonstrates that specific word order options, sometimes in combination with discourse particles, yield meaning effects that are typical for the expressive side of utterances and endow them with an exclamative flavor. Approaching this issue from a syntactic point of view, the book shows that there are syntactic categories (e.g., a certain class of particle verbs) and word orders (e.g., certain fronting patterns involving discourse particles) that directly connect to expressive meaning components. The work presented in this monograph combines theoretical analysis with experimental evidence from both perception and production studies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEmphasis (Linguistics). 4aLinguistische Typologie. 4aSyntax. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aComparative Syntax.  aExpressive Meaning.  aInformation Structure.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Contemporary 2016-2019z978311074297808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2017z9783110547887oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015058670 cprintz978150151503340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150150588140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501505881423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501505881/original  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-074297-8  De Gruyter Mouton Contemporary 2016-2019c2016d2019  a978